feedback:
Your answers to the business questions are in general good. I liked in particular your reasoning about why you would use RMSE - as the project is a regression problem.

You also rightly mentioned Cross validation and overfitting in your answers, which I liked.

I would have liked to see you take into account the value you add by your analysis to the UCONT business for  the question of how you would evaluate the success or failure of your wrk. I think it is always important to relate your performance in what kind of outcome/value you add to the company you work, in this case UCOUNT.

Well Done! In general your answers are good. I would have liked to see a bit more detail reasoning why you particularly choose recall, precision, specificity, and AUC-ROC for this problem instead of say accuracy. 


You are going to use these metrics over and over, so it is better to read more about them and understand their pros and cons.


Also, it is good also to understand clearly what do you want to maximise or minimize in this project? Is high False Negative bad compared to False Positive? Why does that matter?

I liked in particular your answer on how you measure the success and failure of your project. Ultimately if our work is not used to make real impact, it is not a big success.

Well done! I liked how you defined the main objectives, business value, and the steps you  follow.

Although the definition on the metric you use are quite complete, I can't see which one you think is more appropriate and why?

Is the income data analysis a regression or classification problem? Do you use the same metric for both type of projects?

Check this reference for more on that topic 

https://machinelearningmastery.com/classification-versus-regression-in-machine-learning/

Very good! I liked your answer on how you would evaluate the success or failure of your project - only when a data analysis work improves business value or impacts positively society has a real value. 

Your answer on what metric to use is nice, but I would have liked to see you mention in addition  type of problem is the project, classification or regression, and why a certain metric is important. 

See this for more detail

https://machinelearningmastery.com/classification-versus-regression-in-machine-learning/
